# 📝 Git Cheat Sheet

Quick references for essential Git commands — perfect for beginners and contributors.

---

## 🔧 Setup & Configuration
```bash
git config --global user.name "Your Name"       # Set username
git config --global user.email "your@email.com" # Set email
git --version                                   # Check Git version
📂 Starting a Repository
bash
git init                                        # Initialize a new local repo
git clone <repo-url>                            # Clone an existing repo
📌 Tracking & Saving Changes
bash
git status                                      # Show current changes
git add <file>                                  # Stage a file
git add .                                       # Stage all files
git commit -m "message"                         # Commit with a message
🔄 Branching & Merging
bash
git branch                                      # List branches
git branch <name>                               # Create a new branch
git checkout <name>                             # Switch to a branch
git merge <branch>                              # Merge branch into current
🌐 Working with Remotes (GitHub)
bash
git remote add origin <url>                     # Link local repo to GitHub
git push origin main                            # Push changes to GitHub
git pull origin main                            # Pull updates from GitHub
git fetch                                       # Fetch updates without merging
🕵️ Viewing History
bash
git log                                         # Show commit history
git diff                                        # Show differences
🛠️ Undoing & Resetting
bash
git reset <file>                                # Unstage a file
git checkout -- <file>                          # Discard changes in a file
git revert <commit>                             # Undo a commit safely
✅ Quick Workflow
bash
git add . 
git commit -m "message"
git push origin main
📌 Tip: Use this cheat sheet as a quick reference while coding and collaborating on GitHub.

Code

